# Brief Explanation or Implementation Approach

This project is a Movie Recommendation Web App built using React.js with a focus on UI interactivity, filtering, and theme switching.

# Core Features Implemented

1. Movie Listing UI :-

  * Movies are stored in an array inside [App.jsx].
  * Each movie contains title, genre, rating, description, and image.

2. Reusable Component :-

  * [MovieCard] component is used to display each movie dynamically.
  * Props are used to pass movie data.

3. Search Functionality :-

  * Users can search movies by title using a controlled input field
  * Filtering is handled using JavaScript [.filter()]

4. Genre Filtering :-

  * Dropdown allows filtering movies by genre
  * Supports multiple categories like Action, Drama, Comedy, etc.

5. Dark / Light Mode Toggle :-

  * Implemented using React [useState]
  * Theme changes by toggling [body.dark] class
  * CSS handles both light and dark styles smoothly

6. Watchlist Feature :-

  * Each card has a button to add/remove movies from watchlist
  * Managed using local component state

7. Responsive UI :-

  * CSS Grid with [auto-fit] ensures cards align side by side
  * Fully responsive for mobile, tablet, and desktop screens

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Technical Approach

1. React functional components + Hooks (`useState`)
2. Component-based architecture (App + MovieCard)
3. Conditional rendering for theme switching
4. CSS Grid + Flexbox for layout
5. Clean separation of UI and logic

Here in this task i have been deployed an Movie Recommendation Card using funcationality components like props and list rendering components like [.map()] function and css concepts of flex box and grid components. 